gomodel:SYNGO_4178  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig3: BDNF-IR does not colocalize with the synaptic vesicle markers synaptophysin (Dand E) or VGlut (F and G) but colocalises with opioid peptide Met-enkephalin (H-M) and neuropeptide cholecystokinin (N-P).\nFig 4A: Immunogold labelling showed gold clusters to be associated with large vesicles encompassed by an electron-dense membrane.\n\nThe specificity of the antibodies used in the study (anti-myc and anti-BDNF) was validated in previous literature. The anti-Myc antibody specifically detects BDNF as it uses a BDNF knockin line allowing the use of antibodies directed against a tagged version of the BDNF gene (Matsumoto et al., 2008). While the specificity of the anti-BDNF antibody is observed in a line conditionally lacking BDNF in adult neurons (Rauskolb et al., 2010).. Experimental description: For the confocal and EM study, brains were obtained from Bdnf-Myc (Matsumoto et al., 2008) and WT (C57Bl6) respectively." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4178" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

